### 9. **HTTP Server Routes** (`crates/arcand/src/canonical.rs`, lines 121-143)

```rust
pub fn create_canonical_router(runtime: Arc<KernelRuntime>) -> Router {
    let state = CanonicalState { runtime };
    Router::new()
        .route("/health", get(health))
        .route("/sessions", post(create_session))
        .route("/sessions/{session_id}/runs", post(run_session))
        .route("/sessions/{session_id}/state", get(get_state))
        .route("/sessions/{session_id}/events", get(list_events))
        .route("/sessions/{session_id}/events/stream", get(stream_events))
        .route("/sessions/{session_id}/branches", post(create_branch).get(list_branches))
        .route("/sessions/{session_id}/branches/{branch_id}/merge", post(merge_branch))
        .route("/sessions/{session_id}/approvals/{approval_id}", post(resolve_approval))
        .with_state(state)
}
```

**Stream endpoint** (lines 313-379):
- Reads replay buffer from journal (cached events)
- Subscribes to runtime event broadcast
- Streams both replay + live events via SSE
- Supports format negotiation (Canonical, VercelAiSdkV6)

